com.bluegosling.function

Class Predicates

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.bluegosling.function.Predicates

  • public final class Predicates
extends Object
    Numerous utility methods related to using Predicates. This is quite similar to Guava's class of the same name, except these utility methods are for the Java 8 Predicate functional interface as opposed to Guava's interface of the same name.
    See Also:

      • fromFunction

        public static <T> Predicate<T> fromFunction(Function<T,Boolean> function)
        Converts a function into a predicate. Functions return boxed booleans instead of primitives, and thus can return a null. The returned predicate returns true if the function returns true and false otherwise, so a null function result is considered false.
        Parameters:
        function - a function
        Returns:
        the specified function converted to a predicate

      • fromFunction

        public static <T1,T2> BiPredicate<T1,T2> fromFunction(BiFunction<T1,T2,Boolean> function)
        Converts a bivariate function into a bivariate predicate. Functions return boxed booleans instead of primitives, and thus can return a null. The returned predicate returns true if the function returns true and false otherwise, so a null function result is considered false.
        Parameters:
        function - a function
        Returns:
        the specified function converted to a predicate
